Sentencas: The perovskite-type oxides, having a general formula ABO(3), are promising candidates for anode materials in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Dy doped SrTiO3: A promising anodic material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In particular, doped SrTiO3 based perovskites are potential mixed ionic-electronic conductors and they are known to have excellent thermal and chemical stability along with carbon and sulfur tolerance.
Titulo: Dy doped SrTiO3: A promising anodic material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, Dy.Sri,TiO3-delta system with x = 0.03, 0.05, 0.08 and 0.10 is studied to understand the influence of Dy content on its structural and electrical behavior.
Titulo: Dy doped SrTiO3: A promising anodic material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical properties are measured, both in air and hydrogen atmosphere, and structural characterizations are performed before and after electrochemical tests and compared each other to study the stability.
Titulo: Dy doped SrTiO3: A promising anodic material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results show that Dy.Sri,TiO3-delta powders with x < 0.05, are single phase, while for x > 0.08 a small amount of secondary phases is formed.
Titulo: Dy doped SrTiO3: A promising anodic material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In air, the conductivity is predominantly mixed ionic-electronic type for x < 0.05, becoming ionic for x > 0.08.
Titulo: Dy doped SrTiO3: A promising anodic material in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is observed that conductivity, for each composition, increases passing from air to hydrogen and activation energy decreases.
